Masdar Studying Three Locations to Build Wind Farms, Chief Executive Says

-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 
2011-04-05T14:34:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/masdar-studying-three-locations-to-build-wind-farms-chief-executive-says.html
Masdar, the  Abu Dhabi  government-
owned renewable energy company, is studying three locations in
the  United Arab Emirates  in which to build wind power plants,
its chief executive officer said.  Two areas in the northern emirates and the island of Sir
Bani Yas are being considered as locations for wind farms,
Sultan al-Jaber said in Abu Dhabi today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ayesha Daya in Dubai at 
 adaya1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
